article.headline: Colgate over Navy 63-41
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- Austin Tillotson scored 10 points with five assists and grabbed five rebounds in Colgate's 63-41 victory over Navy on Saturday. Murphy Burnatowski and Ethan Jacobs each added 11 points for the Raiders (7-10, 1-5 Patriot). Damon Sherman-Newsome scored 10. Luke Roh led the team with 11 rebounds. The Raiders hit 53.2 percent from the field overall and went 66.7 percent from the line. Brandon Venturini led Navy with 11 points and five rebounds. The Midshipmen (7-10, 2-4) were only 29.3 percent from the field, 25 percent from the line overall and relied heavily on their bench with Zach Fong adding 10 points. Sherman-Newsom's 3-pointer five minutes in capped a 14-0 Colgate run to start the game. The Raiders led 33-15 at halftime. Colgate continued to dominate in the second and a pair of Matt McMullin 3-pointers in the final minutes gave the Raiders a 20-point advantage to finish.
